{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 4 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:1",
      "text": "Hear, ye children, the instruction of a father, and attend to know understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:2",
      "text": "For I give you a good gift; forsake ye not my law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:3",
      "text": "For I also was a son obedient to my father, and loved in the sight of my mother:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:4",
      "text": "who spoke and instructed me, saying, Let our speech be fixed in thine heart, keep our commandments, forget them not:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:5",
      "text": "and do not neglect the speech of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:6",
      "text": "And forsake it not, and it shall cleave to thee: love it, and it shall keep thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:7",
      "text": "Secure it, and it shall exalt thee: honour it, that it may embrace thee;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:9",
      "text": "that it may give unto thy head a crown of graces, and may cover thee with a crown of delight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:10",
      "text": "Hear, my son, and receive my words; and the years of thy life shall be increased, that the resources of thy life may be many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:11",
      "text": "For I teach thee the ways of wisdom; and I cause thee to go in right paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:12",
      "text": "For when thou goest, thy steps shall not be straitened; and when thou runnest, thou shalt not be distressed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:13",
      "text": "Take hold of my instruction; let it not go, —but keep it for thyself for thy life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:14",
      "text": "Go not in the ways of the ungodly, neither covet the ways of transgressors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:15",
      "text": "In whatever place they shall pitch their camp, go not thither; but turn from them, and pass away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:16",
      "text": "For they cannot sleep, unless they have done evil: their sleep is taken away, and they rest not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:17",
      "text": "For these live upon the bread of ungodliness, and are drunken with wine of transgression.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:18",
      "text": "But the ways of the righteous shine like light; they go on and shine, until the day be fully come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:19",
      "text": "But the ways of the ungodly are dark; they know not how they stumble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:20",
      "text": "My son, attend to my speech; and apply thine ear to my words:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:21",
      "text": "that thy fountains may not fail thee; keep them in thine heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:22",
      "text": "For they are life to those that find them, and health to all their flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:23",
      "text": "Keep thine heart with the utmost care; for out of these are the issues of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:24",
      "text": "Remove from thee a froward mouth, and put far away from thee unjust lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:25",
      "text": "Let thine eyes look right on, and let thine eyelids assent to just things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:26",
      "text": "Make straight paths for thy feet, and order thy ways aright.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.4.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:27",
      "text": "Turn not aside to the right hand nor to the left, but turn away thy foot from an evil way: for God knows the ways on the right hand, but those on the left are crooked: and he will make thy ways straight, and will guide thy steps in peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
